parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure - Crossover Valve Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the crossover valve can cause fuel to leak excessively, leading to a potential fire hazard, and in extreme cases, accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the gas tank
fuel pours out while filling up
strong fuel odor inside and outside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks and tank overflows can cause fuel to spill on the ground, creating a fire hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries. In addition, fuel fumes can enter the vehicle, posing a risk to occupants.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from one tank to another
fuel spills out of the fuel filler tube
fuel fumes emitted into the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator wiring harness/plug connection can cause vehicle fires, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: or melting of the wiring harness/plug connection

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause vehicle fires, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: TFI (Thick Film Integrated) Module Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TFI module assembly can cause engine performance issues, stalling, or failure to start, which can lead to accidents or strand the driver.
